@startuml FloraHighLevelArchitecture
title Flora High-Level Architecture

top to bottom direction
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #5F6B5A
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.1
skinparam packageBorderColor #8B9683
skinparam packageBackgroundColor #F7F9F4
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #8B9683
skinparam rectangleBackgroundColor #FCFDFB
skinparam cloudBorderColor #8B9683
skinparam cloudBackgroundColor #F2F5EE
skinparam databaseBorderColor #8B9683
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #FCFDFB

actor "Customer" as customer

package "Client Access" {
  cloud "CloudFront" as cloudfront
  component "React Frontend\nVite + TypeScript\napps/frontend" as frontend
}

package "Application" {
  component "Express Backend API\napps/backend" as backend
  database "PostgreSQL 15\nDocker on EC2" as postgres
}

package "External Services" {
  component "Auth0\nAuthentication" as auth0
  component "Stripe\nPayments + Webhooks" as stripe
  component "Google Gemini\nAI Message Generation" as gemini
  component "SMTP / Gmail\nTransactional Email" as email
}

customer --> cloudfront : HTTPS
cloudfront --> frontend : Serve SPA assets
frontend --> backend : REST API
backend --> postgres : Prisma / SQL

frontend --> auth0 : Login / access token
backend --> auth0 : Verify JWT

backend --> stripe : Payment flows
stripe --> backend : Webhooks

backend --> gemini : Generate messages
backend --> email : Send emails

note right of frontend
Single-page storefront:
- browse products
- manage cart
- checkout
- account actions
end note

note right of backend
Core business API:
- products
- orders
- subscriptions
- users
- AI features
end note

note bottom of cloudfront
CloudFront is the public entry point.
It serves frontend assets and forwards API traffic to the backend.
end note

@enduml
